    "Notably, the model faced challenges in predicting outcomes for drug dosing concentrations lower than 10 nM.",
    "Orita et al. (2020) automated the process of contraction identification and employed a trained SVM to classify hiPSC-CM cultures as normal (experimentally usable) or abnormal (experimentally unusable).",
    "556 brightfield image sequences of beating hiPSC-CMs were captured and classified by experts as abnormal (n = 190) or normal (n = 366).",
    "The contraction properties of the imaged CMs were calculated to be the 200frame simple moving average (SMA) around the frame of interest.",
    "Data augmentation, via the sliding window method, enabled each contraction profile to be split into individual contraction waves, increasing the data set six-fold."
